mdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzAxJn=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB784a13ea" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  said to Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Sridhar Natarajan</a>: Investors want durable=
 earnings, and asset management is the way to give it to them. In the old m=
odel, the reason to invest in Goldman Sachs was that it employed a lot of p=
eople who were good at making investing and trading decisions, and you hope=
d that they=E2=80=99d use that skill to buy stuff <em>for Goldman=C2=A0</em=
>that would go up, leading directly to profits. In the new model, the reaso=
n to invest in Goldman Sachs is that it employs people like that, but it us=
es their=C2=A0skills to buy stuff=C2=A0<em>for clients=C2=A0</em>and charge=
 those clients steady management fees.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mean=
while the traditional core business =E2=80=94=C2=A0the investment bank, now=
 called Global Banking &amp; Markets =E2=80=94 <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30698374.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29sZG1hbnNhY2=
hzLmNvbS9pbnZlc3Rvci1yZWxhdGlvbnMvaW52ZXN0b3ItZGF5LTIwMjMvbXVsdGltZWRpYS9wc=
mVzZW50YXRpb25zL3BkZnMvZ2xvYmFsLWJhbmtpbmctYW5kLW1hcmtldHMucGRm/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB6b99c0fe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> also now emphasizes</a> its =E2=80=9CIncre=
ased Durability of Global Banking &amp; Markets Revenues.=E2=80=9D One thin=
g this means is that financing =E2=80=94=C2=A0basically lending to hedge fu=
nds against their stock and bond portfolios =E2=80=94=C2=A0is a =E2=80=9Cst=
rategic priority for GBM,=E2=80=9D growing from 12% of revenue in 2013 to 2=
2% in 2022. The traditional model of an investment bank=E2=80=99s trading b=
usiness is that clients want to trade stuff, and the bank takes the other s=
ides of those trades; if it is good at that business it will make a lot of =
money, but it is taking market risk on every trade. The new model is that c=
lients want to own stuff, and Goldman will lend them money against that stu=
ff and collect interest: Instead of using its balance sheet to own assets a=
nd take market risk, it will use it to lend against assets, take senior cla=
ims on them, and ideally not lose money on any of them. Obviously <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30698374.259422/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMjkvYXJjaGVnb3Mt=
d2FzLXRvby1idXN5LWZvci1tYXJnaW4tY2FsbHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkY=
mdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzAxJn=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfbd1471a" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  you can mess this up</a> too, but in theory a portfolio of secured loans =
against trading assets should be safer and more boring than a portfolio of =
those assets themselves.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also there is now =
a business called =E2=80=9CPlatform Solutions,=E2=80=9D which you might not=
 guess from the name is what Goldman calls retail banking? (Disclosure: I a=
m also a retail banking customer.)=C2=A0=E2=80=9CPlatform Solutions=E2=80=
=9D sounds like a tech business, one that makes recurring profits by sellin=
g technology to clients without using a lot of balance sheet. =E2=80=9CEmbe=
dding digital platforms in our clients=E2=80=99 ecosystems=E2=80=9D is how =
one slide <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30698374=
.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29sZG1hbnNhY2hzLmNvbS9pbnZlc3Rvci1yZWxhdGlvbnMvaW5=
2ZXN0b3ItZGF5LTIwMjMvbXVsdGltZWRpYS9wcmVzZW50YXRpb25zL3BkZnMvc3RhdGUtb2YtdG=
hlLWZyYW5jaGlzZS5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC632558b6" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> describes=
 the business</a>, but in practice this means a lot of credit-card lending,=
 and it=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30698=
374.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzg4Njk4Mi8w=
MDAxMTkzMTI1MjMwMDg5MDYvZDM4NzQwOWRleDk5MS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3d=
367f16" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> lost money in 2022 due</a> to provisions for credit losses=
. Goldman is retreating from its retail banking efforts, but in a confusing=
 way.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3069837=
4.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMj=
gvZ29sZG1hbi1zLWFsYmF0cm9zcy13ZWlnaHMtb24tc3RvY2stYXMtc29sb21vbi1waXRjaC1ma=
Xp6bGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDEyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3Nv=
dXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB518ebe5d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Natarajan reports</a>:</p><block=
quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chief Executive Officer David Solomon go=
t visibly flustered as analysts pressed him to explain the apparent diverge=
nce between promising to scale up operations such as credit cards and insta=
llment lending, while signaling parts could also be sold.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis is an albatross around Goldman=E2=80=99s neck,=
=E2=80=9D Gerard Cassidy, a banking analyst with Royal Bank of Canada said =
of the consumer business in an interview, adding that it was disheartening =
to hear that it=E2=80=99s not going to break even until 2025.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThey could have come out and said we made an =
error, we are putting it all up for sale, and it=E2=80=99s egg on our face,=
=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CThey could have said we are committed to this b=
usiness and turn it profitable through organic means. But having a blended =
message was a confusing one. Are you going to keep it or are you going to s=
ell it?=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My Bloomberg =
Opinion colleague <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
30698374.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjMtMDMtMDEvZGF2aWQtc29sb21vbi1zLWZhaWxlZC1odW50LWZvci1hLW5ldy1nb2xkbWFuLX=
