<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Greensill</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In early 2021, Credit Suisse Group AG =
had two pretty embarrassing disasters. One was Greensill Capital, a supply-=
chain finance firm started by Lex Greensill. Greensill would provide short-=
term financing to companies that bought goods, and would then sell the loan=
s it made to some Credit Suisse funds. But <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/30698374.259422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDMtMTcvZ3JlZW5zaWxsLWRpZG4tdC1qdXN0LWZpbmFuY=
2UtYmx1ZXN0b25lLXMtc3VwcGx5LWNoYWluP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDEyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMwMSZ1dG1=
fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbe2a79a9" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> it =
turned out</a> that Greensill was actually providing long-term, unsecured f=
inancing to companies against possible future trade receivables, a much ris=
kier business; eventually Greensill collapsed. The other was Archegos Capit=
al Management, a family office run by Bill Hwang. Credit Suisse provided Ar=
chegos with a lot of financing to buy a concentrated, highly leveraged, unh=
edged stock portfolio; when the stocks fell, Archegos collapsed and took a =
lot of Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s money with it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">After Archegos collapsed, Credit Suisse commissioned an internal investi=
gation into what went wrong; it released the report in July 2021. <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30698374.259422/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMjkvYXJjaGVnb3Mt=
d2FzLXRvby1idXN5LWZvci1tYXJnaW4tY2FsbHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkY=
mdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzAxJn=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCfbd1471a" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 We talked about it at the time</a>. It=E2=80=99s a great report. I guess I=
 would summarize it by saying: Credit Suisse understood the risks it was ru=
nning with Archegos, it understood how to fix the situation, and it decided=
 to fix the situation, but it never got around to doing it. Its senior lead=
ers decided that Hwang would need to post more collateral, they told the re=
levant coverage people to ask for more collateral, the coverage people aske=
d for more=C2=A0collateral, but Hwang was busy=C2=A0and they didn=E2=80=99t=
 want to be rude, so they never <em>got=C2=A0</em>the extra collateral, and=
 then Archegos collapsed. Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s failings in Archegos were=
 failings not of understanding but of will; they knew they needed more coll=
ateral but couldn=E2=80=99t bring themselves to demand it forcefully.</p><p=
